A TWO-YEAR-OLD cat has been found dumped in a taped-up pet carrier near communal bins in Glasgow. Abandoned cat appeal A TWO-YEAR-OLD cat has been found dumped in a taped-up pet carrier near communal bins in Glasgow.The Scottish SPCA hit out at the abandonment of the pet, which is believed to have recently had kittens.The two-year-old was found near bins in Gallowgate. Staff at the Lanarkshire rehoming centre have named her Buttercup.Anyone with information should call the SPCA animal helpline on 03000 999 999. 